voice_list.text: I'm not a fan of cleaning, but I do owe this place a lot, so it's okay sometimes...
Ahh, I love it here. I almost wish I could live here.
I want to explore as many places as I can. I might find all sorts of treasures!
I wonder if the things my teachers taught me at the academy will help me in this world, too?
This is someone else's atelier, so I shouldn't make a mess. If I can manage that.
You alchemists never get tired of synthesizing, do you?
I wonder if there's anything weird hidden away in this atelier somewhere.
Haha. Who would have thought poking my nose in random places would lead me to another world.
Adventures are always better with company, right? The more the merrier.
I want to go out on an adventure and look for all sorts of rare things.
So this is the atelier where you do synthesis? Ever caused an explosion?
Phew, this place sure is relaxing. I'd better rest up so I'm ready for the next adventure.
You should take care of your health. Can't do anything if you're not feeling well.
I hope I can make use of the knowledge and experience I've gained during my adventures.
I think we should sell off anything we don't know how to use.
What happens if someone falls off the area outside the atelier?
Do you want me to try collecting some sheet music?
There's so much here I don't know anything about. Everything feels so new.
Alchemy is incredible. We can jump through space just by eating some candy.
Ugh... Investigating costs so much money. Guess it's raw spinach again tonight.
I think we could plant a vegetable garden in this atelier.
Maybe I should open a shop here, too.
I want to eat some yummy carrots. Think we could find some if we went exploring?
I feel like I can do anything when I'm with you all. It's kind of magical.
Money is important, sure, but there are plenty of more important things.
There are so many things I've never seen before. What should I check out next?
Synthesizing together is a good chance to put what I learned at the academy into practice.
Back in my world, there were creatures formed of mana. Is the mana here different?
These requests remind me of the part-time jobs I used to do back at the academy.
The academy's atelier was lively, but even more people come to this one.
There are alchemy books here... Maybe I should read a few.
It's quiet here. Well, at least compared to the atelier I know.
Come to think of it, I don't think I've ever met a serious alchemist until now.
The hem here is getting frayed... I should sew it up when I get a chance.
The minute I graduate, I end up in another world... Will my life ever be normal?
Maybe I should have some pie for a snack today.
This isn't my atelier, so I should try not to make anything explode.
I'd better take care of my staff while we're here. It's tough to do it once we're on the road.
I put some pie into our lunches, what next...? Oh! I think I forgot to wash the dishes!
How did I even get here? Wait! My teacher didn't have anything to do with this, did she?!
This is a strange place I've wound up in. But, I guess I can't really complain.
Hmm... Well, I guess this atelier isn't too bad.
I thought every alchemist was strange, but it seems there are exceptions.
Lazing around is a waste of time. If there's something to do, do it!
I'd better help gather funds. My being a noble means nothing here.
Alchemy books, huh? Oh, some of them have cooking recipes, too. Maybe I'll take a look.
There are so many cool ingredients here, but they're all for synthesis. What a waste!
I wonder how the spices in this world are. Oh, I've got a good idea to test out!
I wonder how alchemists can make food by just mixing stuff in their cauldrons.
With this many people here there's GOT to be at least one chef. That gets me fired up!
Okay, where are we off to today?
I'd better check our schedule.
Working reception at the castle was fine, but it's nice being free to go on adventures.
Rorona was always blowing up her cauldron, but this atelier seems peaceful.
With this many people here, I'm bound to meet one or two interesting people...
What should I synthesize today?
I'd say it's about time for snacks, wouldn't you?
I was a bit nervous around all these strangers, at first. But everyone is so kind. It's nice.
I hope my experience as an adventurer comes in handy in this world.
This isn't my atelier, so I should be careful not to blow up the cauldron.
I like the atmosphere in this atelier.
Maybe I'll take a step outside and get some fresh air.
I know I'm not a princess anymore, but sometimes I still think back to my kingdom and my people.
I gave up on my quest to get stronger, but I guess now I'm back on it?
I've shortened "Meruru's Memos" to "Mememos"! Now then, what's on the schedule today?
I like the atmosphere in this atelier. It's so lively.
It's so cozy that I often end up staying too long...
Everything starts with the basics. Slow and steady will get you where you're headed.
I need to study more about the materials of this world to make good medicine.
I hope Nio isn't making trouble for everyone. I worry about her.
There's a cliff right outside. I refuse to be the one to open the door.
It's difficult to relax when I don't have a mission to work on.
I may be able to complete my mission of making 100 friends here...
I always had these clothes delivered to me every month. But I suppose they can't be delivered here.
I've washed my face, combed my hair... Hmm, it seems these habits have become muscle memory.
Even here, it seems my role hasn't changed much.
People don't suddenly move up the due date for payments here, do they?
So many cute girls here to dress in cute clothes. I'd better work on outfits for everyone.
If I had this many personnel back home, or even just half of this number of people...
It's nice we don't have to risk our lives crossing a desert here.
Is there anything I can help you with?
I desire sweets.
No abnormalities detected in body scan. I am available for requests at any time.
Mild fatigue confirmed in central circuits. I require sweets.
I enjoy this atelier. The number of people coming and going is optimal for boredom prevention.
There are so many great books here. It was worth coming to the atelier just to read them.
What a peculiar atelier. I might need to unravel the secrets of this world to understand it.
The journey to find the truth is long and difficult. There's no end in sight, but I must press on.
Wanderers, huh? I'm not one to make friends, but cooperation seems like the best strategy here.
A world without dusk. I must observe the limits of this world's alchemy.
What should I make today?
I think it's about time for some snacks.
Getting together with everyone here makes me remember my time on the development team.
Something smells sweet... I just had some snacks, so I should probably hold off.
I haven't gotten used to the alchemy here yet, but I'm glad I get to synthesize with Logy.
What should I do today?
That shelf is a bit of a mess.
Using a cauldron for alchemy seems to rely heavily on the senses. I'll have to get used to it.
Being here with everyone reminds me of working on the development team.
I can't forget my sword training. I'll lose my edge if all I do is work.
What should we synthesize next?
The atelier might look eccentric on the outside, but it's mysteriously calming on the inside, isn't it?
I wonder where I should go today. I should ask everyone about their plans.
If we don't take care of our tools, they might fail us when we need them the most.
I'm learning something new here every day. I should review what I've learned at some point.
Looks like we've got visitors. Maybe I should make some tea.
It's tough to practice my singing here.
I love to sing, but I don't have the courage to be the only one doing it.
I need to practice my swordplay. Maybe I can ask someone to help.
It seems they give thanks to the stars here. Prayer is prayer, no matter what form it takes.
I'd like to drink some milk, I think.
Have I gotten shorter...?
It's kind of nice getting to replicate tools that are different from the ones in my world.
I'm glad they have milk in this world. It'd be hard to look for a substitute.
Market research is important. We need to know what's in fashion here.
I bet if we had more plants here, the atmosphere in the atelier would be even better.
I want to make sure everyone who comes here eats enough vegetables.
If I let my guard down I put on weight pretty fast. Well, I lose it pretty fast, too.
It's important to find new places where rare plants can grow.
Got my shovel, got my work gloves, got my tonics. Okay! I'm all ready to head out!
This atelier has an excellent sense of style.
I wonder what kind of new dishes I should make for the cafe.
I need to study the food in this world. It's delicious, and I can use it back at the cafe!
It's actually kind of fun helping alchemists out.
This place feels like it's out of a fairy tale. Wouldn't it be great to have a cafe like this?
Hmm, where should I go next?
Hey, is that the voice of some ore I'm hearing? I wonder where it's coming from?
Heh, if I set up a tent here, I could have an atelier inside an atelier!
Adveeentures, adveeentures, in a brand new wooorld.
An Ice Bomb is— "A blade of frozen judgment"? No, it's more like...
I guess you might say this is like a secret base, too.
I like studying alchemy, but I don't really like studying anything else.
Okay, time to make our next plan. I've got to have as many adventures as possible in this new world!
When I hear everyone talk about their own worlds, I feel like I want to visit them all.
I don't have anyone telling me to help out around the house here... But I kinda miss that.
This is a fun little atelier. It'd give our old secret base a run for its money.
Okay, maybe I'll go outside and do some training.
Part of training is taking care of my sword. Every battle starts with preparation.
Before, even just leaving the island was an adventure. But now I've even gotten used to this whole new world.
I meant to go on this training journey alone, but I keep running into folks I know.
There are so many books here! Are these all alchemy books?
How do you think this atelier was created? I'd love to find some documents about it.
I'd love to just read books all day, but I always end up going on adventures.
The history of this world is full of mysteries. I think there's value in investigating it.
I feel like I've gotten stronger. It's all thanks to Ryza dragging me around on her adventures.
Hm hm hm hm hm hmm.
It's about time to do some cleaning. My hands want to get busy.
Staff, check! Notebook, check! I'm all ready to go!
There's so much to learn every day. It's tough, but it's so fulfilling!
That book I was reading last night was incredible, hehe.
Hm hm hm hm hm hmm.
It's about time to do some cleaning. My hands want to get busy.
It's good to pack light, but be careful you don't get hurt when out gathering. And watch for bugs.
This is a great chance to read! It'd be great to sit here with a book, some tea, some snacks...
I want this atelier to be a place where everyone can come together and have their wishes come true.
We could try making a new alchemy cauldron here...
So well-kept... Nothing like my atelier...
Hey, I'm kind of hungry. Shall I make Sofinancier?
There's so much to learn... I'll bet we can come up with all sorts of new recipes!
Was that who I think it was...? Am I imagining things?
I feel the power of alchemy all around.
This world's alchemy...is so interesting.
We'd better start training for the next exploration.
I may be able to synthesize in my current state if this alchemical system is different.
Soil Potato stew... Hopefully I can recreate the flavors in this world as well.
Unless there's a battle, I just don't care... *Sigh*
Can I take a little nap? Just a little one...
Yep, looking good! We can head out whenever.
You know what? I've become quite the social butterfly. How very unlike the old me.
Ugh... My body is craving movement... I need to get moving!
Unless there's a battle, I just don't care... *Sigh*
Can I have a little nap? Just a little one...
This is so much easier to move around in. Hmm, I wonder if we can make it even lighter...
Wearing light armor, you have to pay more attention to the enemy's movements. Wouldn't want to get hurt and worry everyone again.
Maybe I should read up on alchemy... I wonder where I could get my hands on an alchemy book...
Shall we take a break over a spot of tea?
I need to learn more so I can help out where I can with alchemy.
To think that we can all travel together again so soon... To have an adventure with so many new people...
I wonder if anyone coming likes music? I'd love to do a performance for everyone someday.
Capital distribution channels, procurement prices... These will all need further research.
I'd better return the book I borrowed.
What shall I synthesize today?
Is my hat sitting straight? Ah, perfect!
I hope I can put the things I learned at the academy to use in this world as well.
We should double check our plans. We have to make the most of our time.
Oh, but maybe if I do it this way...
Why not have a little break?
All right. Now that we have some time to ourselves, let's go over our plans.
There's so much to learn every day. Reminds me of when I first started alchemy.
I just can't help myself. I have to check to see if there's anyone I know.
What a lovely atelier!
I might go outside for some fresh air.
Heehee! I feel like going out somewhere in this dress.
Royal etiquette lessons are so dull, but I suppose there's a time and a place for them.
I'd like to get moving a little. Just a little should be all right?
I feel the power of alchemy all around.
This world's alchemy...is so interesting.

A festival where you wear scary costumes and ask for candy?
Never heard of such a strange custom.
As a doll, I can eat as much candy as I like and it will never affect my body.
People usually associate carving lanterns with pumpkins, but apparently some regions use turnips.
I wonder what kind of mechanisms are at work in this Atelier.
Quite comfortable here, isn't it?

Do witches exist in this world, too?
I wonder...
My daily training is essential to become a great witch like my great-great-grandmother.

What kind of training shall I do today?
There's so much I want to do!
Where exactly is this Atelier situated?
Hmm, I'm getting a little hungry...

I wonder if Ayesha had a proper meal today.
She gets sucked into her work all day long when I leave her alone.
I have to study a lot and gain experience so that I don't worry Ayesha and the others!

Going to all sorts of places and meeting all sorts of people...
Each and every day is so much fun!
I'm getting a little hungry. Maybe I should make something.
It's so lively and fun here!

I think my circle of friends has expanded since I came here.
I'm so happy because it feels like my family has grown.
Seeing as I've come all the way to a different world, I think I'll try my hand at some jobs other than excavation.

Everyone tries so hard, even though they're young.
I won't lose to their spirit!
An Atelier that doesn't leak when it rains? I'm envious.
Hehe! Which book should I delve into next?

I also have to practice my art.
I refuse to be called a scribbler!
The way to adjust the cauldron temperature, the angle of the stirring rod... What else is different?

It's like I'm inside some sort of mysterious painting.
I can't believe this place exists!
Teehee, what mischief shall I get up to next?
I wonder how much it cost to build this Atelier.

Boo! Why are there no comics?
Wait... Don't tell me they don't even exist in this world?

Guided by the stars?
Ooh, make me rich! Make me rich!

I should review my ambition notebook later.
I wonder if I've achieved anything.
In a way, this place is like a little hideaway, isn't it?
I enjoy alchemy, but I don't really like studying anything else...
Hehe. When I wear these glasses, I feel like I'm a little bit smarter.
When I wear this outfit it somehow makes me crave sweets...

"Alchemy is the art of creating something from nothing."
Hmm, that didn't come across as impressive as I'd hoped...
I think I'll treat myself to a sweet.
This Atelier itself may very well be evidence of high-level alchemy.

The good and bad of alchemy...
It would seem this world has a darker side as well.
I'd love to leave the practical synthesis to the younger alchemists, but I can't relax just yet.

An Atelier where alchemists gather?
The old me would never have come near such a place.

There's a limit to who can come here?
It's a good place to hide from enemies.
I'd like to get rid of the sweets, but if the others enjoy them, I guess they can stay.

I've had a lot more opportunities to train apprentices lately.
Perhaps I should retrain myself as well.
Izana shows great potential. She says she wants to be a knight, but she'd also make a great warrior.
If the Apexi are going to affect the world, then I'll hunt them down myself.
It used to be just Resna, Saskia, and me, but now it's much more lively around here.
Instead of just sitting around, I'll do some squats right here and get into shape!

I've got to keep my hammer in perfect condition!
Ham~mer Ham~mer
The basics of blacksmithing: first is the hammer, second is the hammer, and third, fourth, and fifth are also the hammer!
I'm not very good at studying, but I'll try my best so I can become a knight!
Hm hm hm hm hm hmm.
I should get to cleaning, I suppose. Time to roll up my sleeves!

Such a cute and fluffy outfit!
Though it might be a little showy.
I need to put my all into today's synthesis so that we can spread happiness to everyone. Let's go!
I wonder what the inspiration behind this outfit was. I'll have to look it up later.
I need to do some sewing or take lessons from time to time to maintain my noble taste...
No matter where I look, the Atelier is bustling. Is that just a coincidence, I wonder?
I've never worn festival clothes before, so this is quite a refreshing change.

Trying to bring smiles to everyone is challenging.
But it feels like it's going to be a valuable experience.

I've stopped worrying about what others think of me.
Getting used to that is kind of scary.
I'm not really good at cleaning, but I've gotten so much out of this place. It's only fair to help out sometimes...
This place is just so comfy! I could see myself living here.

I moved things around a bit to make it easier to get around.
Now I can gather and synthesize with no trouble at all!
Putting this outfit on was a bit of a pain, but now that it's on, it makes me feel ready for anything!

I'm surprised to find a place where this sort of outfit fits in.
Never came across anything like it back in Salburg.
This atelier is so lively, with a great atmosphere.
It's so cozy that I often end up staying too long...
I would never have even imagined that my medicine would one day be used in the royal palace.

I wonder if I'm being too protective of Nio.
That said, she did do something pretty dangerous recently...

There were a lot of books on alchemy in the royal library.
They might be of use to everyone.

I'd love to join everyone for a feast, but I'll hold out for now.
Endurance is something I'm known for.

This atelier truly is a treasure trove!
I never tire of being here.

The most important part of any adventure is having the right information.
I'll be sure to research our next destination!

I may not have a knack for alchemy,
but meeting such remarkable people has been a far greater boon.

I never thought this world would have so many wanderers.
There's no end to the fascinating conversations we could have.
What should I synthesize next?
The atelier might look eccentric on the outside, but it's mysteriously calming on the inside, isn't it?

Is my ribbon crooked?
Nope, looks fine!
It might be fun to have Lotte try on one of my family's traditional outfits next time. Teehee.

My legs feel a bit chilly.
I wonder if I'll get used to it after a while...
It's time to get to work! Can't miss that deadline!
Okay, let's get to it!

Trala, tralala la! Shallotte!
Giving her best even in another world!

I can use anything in this huuuge Atelier however I want?
That's super generous!

Looks like the floor's a bit dirty?
I'm pretty good at cleanin', so leave it to me!
Alchemy is so very beautiful.
My tummy's starting to rumble a little.

My, just look at this mess...
It'll feel great to clean this up!
Such a lively and delightful place, all thanks to the people gathering here.

I better make sure I'm doing my part.
Believe it or not, I used to work at a big company back in the day!
The scenery beyond here is like something from another world.

I hope His Highness isn't causing any trouble.
I must keep a close eye on him.

My daily training is essential.
I'll be careful not to get in anyone's way.

Warriors from another world?
I'd love to exchange martial techniques with them.
There's even a martial technique that imitates the movements of wild beasts. Roar!
What to do today...
That shelf is a bit messy.

It seems there are others researching the Apexi.
Collecting information here has been a big help.

Dragon slaying?
Felling a dragon isn't something a person should do alone.

I hear stories from many different worlds.
It seems that no matter where you go, you'll find hardworking people.
I wonder what I should make today.
About time for a little snack...
Hmm. I feel a bit restless without my tail...
I've always wanted to wear an outfit like this. It comes together so nicely!

Welcome home, Master!
Just kidding. Haha.
What should I synthesize today?
Perhaps it's time to have a snack!
You know, I've never really been around many composed and mature women.
Just changing my outfit doesn't make me more mature. I need to change from the inside out!
When it's cold, this outfit makes adventuring a lot easier. Wait, do I need my usual clothes at all...?
Hmm, which pie should I have today?
This isn't my Atelier, so I need to be careful not to cause any explosions...
I tried dressing a bit more like a grown-up. I kind of like how it looks!
I should try to match my behavior to my outfit! Maybe I'll start by making a bittersweet pie today.
I've always had to wear clothes Master Astrid liked, so I don't really know if this will suit me...but I have to believe in myself!
I recently saw someone with a book that told a tale of knights. It looked as though the owner truly treasured it.
I have often been told that I look intimidating. I wonder if that's how people here see me too.
I'm surprised to see so many alchemists gathered here. I hope they won't be too reckless while they're all together.
In Arland, there was such a civilization known as the Machina, but they don't seem to be around here much.
A Knight of the Midnight Sun, was it? The knights who protect the royal family are very special.
I just can't find the motivation for anything other than fighting. So tired...
Can I take a nap? Just for a little bit.
Hmm. This outfit feels like it'll be easy to fight in. Makes me feel full of energy. In Resna's words, "Yaaah!"
Getting beaten up just isn't me. I'll always be there to fight back! That's what this outfit is for!
When I asked Resna what she thought about this outfit, she said it was "cute." Actually made me blush a little.
An Atelier that doesn't leak when it rains? I'm jealous.
Hehe, which book should I delve into next?
No matter how scared I am, remembering the promise I made to my mother always gives me courage.
If this power was ever used to play pranks, it would be a disaster. I better keep a veeery close eye on Sue.
Hehe, wearing this outfit makes me feel so light. It's like I'm about to take off into the skies!
This place is actually quite cozy. There are so many different people, it feels so alive!
This is my imitation of Valeria when she's hungry: "Ooh, need food! Food, fooood!" I'm not even exaggerating.
This outfit makes me feel light on my feet. Might be perfect for sneaking around.
I wasn't sure if this kind of outfit would suit me... but it turns out it looks pretty good on me!
I should try not to just rely on my partner all the time. Time for some training! Just a little, though!
Hmm, where should I go next?

Hmm? I think I hear some ore...
Where's that coming from?
I've worn many outfits on my travels, but this is the first one that makes me feel so light on my feet!
If I had to name this outfit, how about "The Winged Battledress Bestowed by the Black Rose"?
I'd like to try making a bed with these floating roses. Oh, a flying alchemy cauldron would be fun too!
Alchemy is so beautiful every time I see it. It's mesmerizing!
Hmm, what should be on the menu today?
This outfit is so light and easy to move around in. Not to mention it looks so cute! Definitely one of my favorites!
Would this outfit draw attention if I wore it while peddling? Maybe I'll think about it after the fighting calms down...
Before the fight begins, I need to make sure my weapon is in good condition.
Teehee, what mischief shall I get up to next?
I wonder how much it cost to build this Atelier...
When I feel like giving up, I remember the promise I made to my mom. It always brings back my motivation!
This outfit apparently has the power to combat the Apexi, but I do wonder if I can use it for normal battles too...
Hehe, when I wear this outfit my charm levels go through the roof! I'm practically invincible!
I should clean up the club room while I have the chance. I want to keep things tidy for everyone!
If there was no curfew, I would stay in the club room forever...
Hehe, I'm looking forward to today's club activities! Can't wait to try all sorts of things!
Ugh, I hate that I have to study for normal subjects as well. There's so much to do, it's overwhelming.
I still can't believe I got into this academy. I need to work hard to become an alchemist!
Resna sure loves cleaning. The club room is so tidy it's unsettling...
What can I do to help as a senior? I can't think of much except for my alchemy skills.
I hope the kids are okay. I also hope they aren't being reckless again...
I can't wait to get home and see my dolls. What game shall we play today?
"Boss" this, "Boss" that... Can everyone please stop calling me that?
Cute juniors, kind classmates, reliable teachers. Simply put, our club is the best, isn't it?
Once Mimi gets here, I'll have to try out this recipe. I'm sure she'll enjoy it!
Even more veggies arrived from home! I haven't even finished the last batch yet. What am I gonna do with all these?
Isn't there anything interesting to do? I want a thrilling adventure that gets the heart racing!
The new students this year are all so cute! I need to do my best as their senior!
Honestly, why is she always like this...
Hmm? Some of the ingredients I collected are missing... Did Ryza use them for cooking again?!
Another letter from my parents. I've told them they don't need to send money, but they just worry too much.
This recipe feels like it's missing something... Maybe I should ask Ryza for some advice.
I'm getting used to dorm life, and the Alchemy Club isn't as bad as I thought. This could be quite fun!
I think I outdid myself with today's snack. I hope everyone likes it.
As a member of this team, I have to make sure I'm pulling my weight too!
What sort of sweets should I make today? I wonder if Ryza would like a veggie pie.
Hair, check. Uniform, check. Packed bag, check! 'Kay, I'm ready to head out any time.
This team sure has gotten rowdier since Resna and the others joined...
Following the curriculum is a given, but having a library this expansive calls for a bit of self-study, too.
At the end of the day, life at the academy is pretty good.
I'm not great at talking to people...but that doesn't mean I don't want to try.
Academy life, huh? What am I doing here?
At first, I didn't have much interest in alchemy. But now...
Shall we take a little tea break?
I need to learn more about alchemy so I can help out where I can.
I was told this is a special outfit worn at festivals. Oh, I'd love for Ryza to wear one with me!
I'm not used to wearing clothes like these... I hope I'm doing them justice.
This outfit is a bit of a process to put on, but it's surprisingly cool and comfortable to wear.
Alchemy, huh. If I use that, maybe I can build a sturdier ship.
There's a lot I don't understand 'round here. I just hope Valeria doesn't break anything...
Seein' them so fired up makes me wanna chase my own dreams again.
I owe it all to my little angel for keeping me going like this. Really can't thank her enough.
Surprisingly, there're a lot of people who know their way 'round a ship. I thought it was just Totori.
What should I read? There's always so much to learn.
The open seas are still full of the unknown. I want to gather more information.
I never imagined that I would be able to go adventuring by ship in this world too!
Lanze reminds me of my shipwright father in some ways, so I can't help but look out for him.
My experience as an adventurer fighting monsters aboard a ship will definitely be useful in this world!
I really don't like cleaning...but since I'm a guest here, I guess I should help out sometimes...
This place is so cozy! Cozy enough to want to live here.
This outfit is so easy to move around in, I should go exploring! Although I guess I already do that all the time.
In my world, there's an annual martial tournament. Thinking about it brings back all sorts of memories.
This outfit makes me feel like jumping into action! Hiyah! Ah! Oopsie... I bumped into something.
The scenery out here... It's like a whole different world.
I need to keep an eye on His Highness to make sure he doesn't cause any trouble...
This armor is much lighter than my knight's armor. I do feel a bit vulnerable, though...
Hehe, you think it suits me? Ah! *Ahem* Never mind.
Someone just called my outfit cute. Can you believe them? Heh.
Well then, maybe I should do some cooki—no. I think I'll leave that to someone else.
Being here makes me feel like I'll be roped into helping with my worst fear...paperwork.
